# License Guide

This repository uses a **dual license** scheme so that source code samples
remain maximally reusable, while educational text content is protected from
unauthorized commercial repackaging.

> 🇯🇵 本リポジトリは **デュアルライセンス** を採用しています。コードは自由に再利用でき、
> 教育的な文書コンテンツは無断商用利用を制限しています。

---

## Quick Summary / 概要

| Content Type / 対象 | License | File |
|---|---|---|
| **Source code** — `*.py`, `lab.py`, `scripts/`, code cells in notebooks (`*.ipynb`), config files | **MIT License** | [`LICENSE-CODE`](LICENSE-CODE) |
| **Documentation** — `*.md`, markdown cells in notebooks, columns, glossaries, figures | **CC BY-NC-SA 4.0** | [`LICENSE-DOCS`](LICENSE-DOCS) |

---

## Why Dual License? / なぜ分けるのか

### Code (MIT)

The code samples are intentionally simple and educational. Use them in your own
projects — commercial or otherwise — with no friction. Just keep the MIT notice.

> コードはサンプルなので、商用・非商用を問わず自由に使ってください。
> MIT ライセンス表記だけは残してください。

### Documentation (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)

The explanations, columns, structural design, glossaries, and editorial choices
represent significant authorial effort. They are licensed for **non-commercial
use only**, with attribution, and any derivative works must use the same license.

> 解説・コラム・構造設計・用語集・編集判断には相応の労力が投じられています。
> **非商用利用のみ** 許可し、改変版も同条件で公開してください。

You **MAY**:
- ✅ Read, share, and redistribute for personal study and education
- ✅ Adapt, translate, or remix for non-commercial purposes
- ✅ Use AI tools (Claude / Gemini / Codex etc.) to extend or customize
- ✅ Use in classrooms, study groups, and academic teaching (non-paid)

You **MAY NOT** (without prior written permission):
- ❌ Sell, repackage, or commercialize the content (book publication, paid courses, paid SaaS, etc.)
- ❌ Use for paid corporate training or revenue-generating workshops
- ❌ Strip the attribution and republish as your own
- ❌ Re-license under more permissive terms (e.g., MIT) to circumvent NC restrictions

---

## File Classification / ファイル区分の判定

When in doubt:

| File extension / location | Treated as |
|---|---|
| `*.py`, `*.toml`, `*.yml`, `*.yaml`, `*.json`, `Makefile`, shell scripts | **Code** (MIT) |
| `*.md`, `*.txt`, image files (`*.png`, `*.svg`, etc.) created for this repo | **Documentation** (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) |
| `*.ipynb` notebooks | **Mixed** — code cells under MIT, markdown cells under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 |
| Third-party content (cited papers, external images) | Original author's license; see in-text citation |

---

## Commercial Use / 商用利用について

Want to use this content for any commercial purpose (book, paid course,
corporate training, paid SaaS, resale, etc.)?

See [`DISCLAIMER.md`](DISCLAIMER.md) for the contact channel. Commercial
licenses are negotiated case by case.

> 商用利用 (書籍化・有料講座・企業研修・有償配布等) をご希望の場合は、
> [`DISCLAIMER.md`](DISCLAIMER.md) の窓口経由でご相談ください。
> ケースバイケースで個別に有償許諾します。

